* Audio decoding
    FFmpeg is used as a local command-line executable for audio decoding
    and format conversion. Windows builds bundle a BtbN FFmpeg "lgpl"
    build and treat it as LGPLv3 because the build includes
    --enable-version3. The bundled build is checked to exclude
    --enable-gpl, --enable-nonfree, libx264, libx265, libxvid, and
    libfdk-aac.
    Build project: https://github.com/BtbN/FFmpeg-Builds
    FFmpeg source: https://github.com/FFmpeg/FFmpeg
    Build metadata and hashes are provided in resources/ffmpeg/
    FFMPEG_BUILD_INFO.txt. LoTT distribution Python environments do not
    include PyAV ("av") or imageio-ffmpeg; faster-whisper is installed
    without dependency-resolving PyAV into the distribution environment.

